# Skills and external tools

Realms tooling lives under **`~/.claude/plugins/...`** (Superpowers, frontend-design, etc.). **Read the skill file** when the task matches — do not cargo-cult skill names without opening them.

## Quick routing

| Situation | Skill / tool |
|-----------|----------------|
| New feature or system design | `superpowers:brainstorming` → `writing-plans` |
| Bug / failing test | `superpowers:systematic-debugging` |
| Compose UI build or redesign | `frontend-design:frontend-design` |
| Multi-file feature | `feature-dev:feature-dev` or `writing-plans` |
| Parallel independent tasks | `dispatching-parallel-agents` / subagents |
| Game mechanics / reducers / parser | `test-driven-development` |
| Before claiming done | `verification-before-completion` (align with project verify rules) |
| User asks to commit / PR | `commit-commands:*` if available |
| Major feature / merge | `requesting-code-review`, `finishing-a-development-branch` |
| PR feedback | `receiving-code-review` |
| Git isolation | `using-git-worktrees` |
| Live library docs | **Context7** MCP (`plugin-context7-context7`) when APIs may be stale |

## Code review / hooks (optional)

`code-review:code-review`, `pr-review-toolkit:review-pr`, `hookify:*` — use when the user wants automation or hooks, not by default.

## Context7 MCP

Use for up-to-date docs: Compose, Kotlin serialization, Robolectric, Gradle Kotlin DSL, provider APIs, etc.
